## The UI/UX overhaul and the design system

Only after securing this technical base and validating the reliability of the raw data did I tackle the visual product. I built my own design system from scratch — typography, a starry dark theme, components — to replace the initial prototype with an interface meant to stay readable mid-effort. The ergonomics were tested and validated in real conditions by people close to me, directly on the machine.

## Where it stands and the end goal

RØDD today ships full training programmes as well as classic sessions. The biggest technical job was aligning and calibrating my local data to get unified, reliable metrics, modelled on Concept2's precision standards. Right now I am finishing the immersive challenges (such as GPS tracking on Lake Annecy).

RØDD's end goal is clear: to carry this project, solo, all the way through its life cycle — which means a full, official App Store release.

This technical series will run three or four articles. In the next one, we will get straight to the heart of it: in-depth analysis of the Bluetooth logs, precise reverse-engineering of the firmware's FTMS characteristics, and the implementation of the abstraction layer on top of `CoreBluetooth`.

